  <!-- Sections -->
  <h2 id="intro">Introduction to Anchor Tag</h2>
  <p>
    The <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> tag in HTML is used to define hyperlinks. 
    It allows users to navigate from one page to another or jump within the same page. 
    You can also use the <code>title</code> attribute to provide extra information 
    when hovering over a link.
  </p>

  <h2 id="example">Anchor Tag Example</h2>
  <p>
    Here‚Äôs a simple example of an anchor tag:
  </p>
  <pre>
&lt;a href="https://www.example.com" title="Go to Example Website"&gt;
  Visit Example
&lt;/a&gt;
  </pre>
  <p>
    Try it here üëâ 
    <a href="https://www.example.com" title="Go to Example Website">Visit Example</a>
  </p>

  <h2 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h2>
  <p>
    Anchor tags make the web interconnected. You can link to external websites, 
    internal sections, or even add a ‚ÄúBack to Top‚Äù button.
  </p>

